September 14 – Early dismissal for students

September 23 - PreACT test for juniors
September 21 – 25 – Homecoming week

post_text:
CPS Families and Community

We have canceled tonight’s high school football game against McCook. With one confirmed positive COVID-19 case on the high school football team and multiple other players showing symptoms, we believe this is best for everyone’s safety. We are working closely with Public Health Solutions and will provide more information if and when it becomes available. Thank you for your patience and understanding.

Familias y comunidad de las Escuelas Públicas de Crete

Hemos cancelado el partido de fútbol de la escuela secundaria de esta noche contra McCook. Con un caso de COVID-19 positivo confirmado en el equipo de fútbol de la escuela superior y muchos otros jugadores que muestran síntomas, creemos que esto es lo mejor para la seguridad de todos. Estamos trabajando en estrecha colaboración con Public Health Solutions y brindaremos más información cuando esté disponible. Gracias por su paciencia y comprensión.

"The Crete Men's Soccer team is submitting an order for masks and Gaiters on August 28th. https://cretesoccer.com This was originally just for players, coaches, and parents but we have heard that these are quite popular and have been asked by several students how they could order them. If you would like to purchase a Crete FC mask or Gaiter there are 2 ways to do so. The first is to stop in and pick up an order form and return it with cash to the office by August 28th. The second is to order online by using a credit card at https://cretesoccer.com
Orders are due by 3:30pm August 28th and should be available for
pickup in 3 weeks or so."

Thank you and have a great rest of your week!

post_text:
Cardinal Fans/Parents - With the change in open house plans, we have rescheduled our Spirit Button Photos.

Amanda Nohavec will once again be taking photos and creating buttons for Crete fans.

Photos this year will be on Wednesday, Aug. 12 from 5:30 - 7:30 p.m. near the loading dock on the north side of the High School.

Students should receive order forms at practice Tuesday afternoon or Wednesday morning.The form is also attached to this email.

If you can, please print and complete the form and send it with payment to the school with your child for their photo.

Social distancing protocols will be followed.

Please email if you have any questions.

Additionally, at this time due to the being in a "yellow" stage on the COVID risk dial, we have suspended plans for the fall kickoff event.

Please follow us on Facebook and Twitter for event updates as things progress.

Thank you!

CPS STAFF RETIREMENT DRIVE-BY PARADE
Crete Community - As many of you know, Jim Moore, Chuck McGinnis, Julie Schumacher, Faith Keller and Karen Drevo are retiring from Crete Public School after many years of dedicated service. If you would like to show your appreciation to them for their years of service, please drive through the High School parking lot and back Intermediate School parking lot on Friday, May 15, between 6:00-7:00 p.m.

The retirees will be present so feel free to roll down your window and give them a shout, honk your horn and show them how much we appreciate them and how much they will be missed!

For the safety of our staff, students, and community, Grab N Go meals will change to once a week curbside pick up at limited locations beginning Monday, May 11th.

Every Monday from May 11th to June 29th children between the ages of 1-18 will be provided seven breakfasts, seven lunch meals, and a gallon of milk.

Pick up locations will be at Crete Elementary (main entrance, door #1), Crete Middle School (bus pick up lot, door #4), Denton, Hallam, and Sprague from 11:00-1:00 and 4:00-6:00.

I wanted to give you a heads up about a site we created called Nebraska Seniors

We have a site link just for Crete seniors offering a custom Senior sign and some t-shirts!

https://stores.inksoft.com/nebraska_seniors/shop/products/crete_high_school?page=1

So far we have 33 High Schools we will have represented on this site. We wanted to give the family a chance to recognize their seniors during this unusual school year.

The tshirts on the site are the same for every school in their school colors, in hopes of uniting the state as a whole.

I would appreciate it if you would be willing to share the site with any families who may have a senior this year!

We will be open on this initial run until May 4th until 9am, but we will run a second time after that.

I hope you are both well out in Crete!

Thank you,

Alyssa Kaufhold
Sales Representative- Schools
akaufhold@artfxscreenprinting.com

St James School is offering free meals for children beginning Wednesday, April 15. You do not need to be a member of their parish or go to their school to receive a meal, this is open to all children ages 1-18 in our community.

They know this is a difficult time for many, so they hope a warm meal can offer some peace to you and your family.

Volunteers will practice safe social distancing while handing meals out in the alley between the church and the school.

Children do not need to be present to receive a meal, but they ask that you only take what is needed for your family.

Meals are available each evening until they run out.

shared_text:
Crete Public Schools PTO- Elementary and Intermediate School
April 14 at 2:20 PM ·

Thank you everyone for your patience as we adapt our plant sale pickup during the COVID-19 pandemic. The pickup will now be May 8th from 4-8pm. In the next couple of weeks, we will send out a Sign-Up Genius so that you may sign up for a time to pick up your plants. We still need to adhere to the safety measures that are in place for the state, so we will be very strategic. Pick-up will now be at the old ShopKo building. Each car will have a designated time slot, that you have chosen. You will drive up , and stay in your car, while a volunteer will load your plants into your car. The plants and flowers will already be pre-sorted by orders, to make it easy for pick-up. While you won't be able to choose all of your items, we are allowing people to choose their hanging baskets, planters and max planters. Please look for more information as we get closer. Please stay safe and thank you for working with us.

Good evening CPS families this is your superintendent Dr. McDowell with an important COVID-19 Update.

Today the Governor and Commissioner of Education informed us that all schools must close no later than March 23, 2020. As planned, students will return to class on Wednesday, March 18. This is a very important day for our students as our teachers and staff have worked hard to provide enrichment opportunities for our students during an extended closure. Crete Public Schools will be closed indefinitely beginning Thursday, March 19, 2020, this includes all activities and CCLC. We will continue to work with local and state health officials, the Governor's office and NDE to determine a reopening day. A detailed letter is available via our website, email, and social media.

Thank you for your patience as we continue to work through this unprecedented event.

Buenas tardes familias de las escuelas públicas de Crete, este es un mensaje del Dr. McDowell con una actualización importante.

Las escuelas continúan colaborando ampliamente con funcionarios de salud pública, el Departamento de Educación de Nebraska, la oficina del gobernador y otros distritos escolares del área. Se cancelan las clases y los programas de CCLC el lunes 16 de marzo y el martes 17 de marzo. Las actividades extra curriculares de la escuela superior continuarán según lo programado originalmente. Todo el personal se reporta ambos días para prepararse para un posible cierre extendido, según la información de nuestra colaboración. Continuamos monitoreando esta situación que cambia rápidamente y lo mantendremos actualizado. En este momento, las clases empiezan de nuevo el miércoles 18 de marzo.

Una actualización detallada está disponible a través de nuestro sitio web, correo electrónico y medios de comunicación social.

Good evening CPS families,

CPS continues to collaborate extensively with public health officials, NDE, the Governor’s office (DHHS), and other area school districts about COVID-19. Classes and CCLC are canceled for Monday, March 16 and Tuesday, March 17. High school extra-curricular activities will continue as originally scheduled. All staff will report both days to prepare for a possible extended closure, based on information from our partners. We continue to monitor this rapidly changing situation and will keep you updated. At this time, classes will resume Wednesday, March 18.

A detailed update is available via our website, email, and social media outlets.

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work through this dynamic situation.

Sincerely,

Dr. McDowell

Sending on behalf of State CTE Director, Katie Graham.
The message below was sent to all Superintendents earlier this evening.

Kristin
------
We continue to get updated information regarding COVID-19 from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and Nebraska health officials. In light of the current health issues and precautions taken to prevent the spread of the novel coronavirus, we have made the difficult decision to cancel all Career and Technical Student Organization (CTSO) 2020 State Leadership Conference/Conventions and associated large gatherings and events. While a variety of factors influenced this decision, be assured that the health and safety of our students and stakeholders is always our primary concern.

This includes:

· DECA (March 18-21)
· HOSA (March 22-24)
· Educators Rising (March 25)
· FBLA (March 30-April 1)
· FFA (April 1-3)
· SkillsUSA (April 2-4)
· FCCLA (April 5-7)

From the desk of Jeff Stauss:

All,

The NSAA is aware of the fluidity of COVID-19 and the potential impact hosting statewide events could have regarding the on-going public health threat. Many of our member schools are making decisions in the best interest of their student participants, coaches and communities. The NSAA is regretfully suspending district and state speech contests until further notice.

This is an unprecedented event. The NSAA Board of Directors and staff understand the hardship this has created for our membership. The NSAA will use this time to evaluate potential alternatives and the next steps for moving forward.

Sincerely,
Jeff Stauss
Assistant Director
Nebraska School Activities Association

post_text:
Footloose -
When Ren and his mother move from Chicago to a small farming town, he is prepared for the inevitable adjustment period at his new high school. But he’s not prepared for the rigorous local edicts, including a ban on dancing instituted by the local preacher, who is determined to exercise control over the town’s youth. When the reverend’s rebellious daughter sets her sights on Ren, her roughneck boyfriend tries to sabotage Ren’s reputation, with many of the locals eager to believe the worst about the new kid. The heartfelt story that emerges pins a father longing for the son he lost against a young man aching for the father who walked out on him.

High School Musical Tickets

Footloose -
When Ren and his mother move from Chicago to a small farming town, he is prepared for the inevitable adjustment period at his new high school. But he’s not prepared for the rigorous local edicts, including a ban on dancing instituted by the local preacher, who is determined to exercise control over the town’s youth. When the reverend’s rebellious daughter sets her sights on Ren, her roughneck boyfriend tries to sabotage Ren’s reputation, with many of the locals eager to believe the worst about the new kid. The heartfelt story that emerges pins a father longing for the son he lost against a young man aching for the father who walked out on him.

The shopper online store link to order tickets beginning March 3 is: https://search.seatyourself.biz/webstore/accounts/cretehs/buy-tix?d=0

NATIONAL READ ACROSS AMERICA DAY (DR. SEUSS DAY)
Each year, National Read Across America Day is celebrated on March 2nd, the birthday of Dr. Seuss. The annual event is part of Read Across America, an initiative on reading creative by the National Education Association. The event is designed to encourage reading in children and is fostered through the schools. This motivational and awareness day calls all children and youth in every community across the United States to celebrate reading. It encourages them to read wherever they are.

Hello Cardinal Union Friends!
We will be hosting a blood drive this Thursday from 4-7pm in the Crete High School parking lot in the mobile unit.
This blood drive is open to the public and we are offering these times to help support the Science Club's blood drive Friday during the school day for staff and students.

Nebraska is dangerously low on blood supply and we need all the donors we can get!
Walk ins are also welcome, however we encourage appointments.

To schedule an appointment you can do any of the following:

schedule online at : bit.ly/cretehighblooddrive
Call: 402-826-9856
Email: tina.rockenbach@creteschools.org

Parents and Guardians
Our school uses the SchoolMessenger system to deliver messages with important information about events, school closings, safety alerts and more.
In the next week, we will be sending home information about our "opt-in process" for participants to receive text messages on this system. Please keep an eye out for these important documents to be coming home with your child.
To comply with wireless carrier requirements and protect against unsolicited text messages, you will also be receiving a text message on your wireless cell phone number which our district has on file for you requesting you "opt-in" to receive important information from our district via our SMS text messaging service.
So that you may continue to receive these important messages by text message, we encourage you to reply with "Y" or "Yes" when you receive such a verification message. If you do not reply, you will not receive any further text messages from our schools.

post_text: Crete FBLA is celebrating National FBLA Week February 2nd-8th. For over 50 years, FBLA has been one of the largest and most active student organizations at Crete High School. With 65 members this year, FBLA is continuously active in the school and community including Breakfast with Santa, Crete Backpack Program, the Nebraska FBLA Foundation, March of Dimes, and much more. Over the past year members have traveled to Fall Leadership & State Leadership Conferences in Omaha, National Leadership Conference in San Antonio, and National Fall Leadership Conference in Denver. Thanks to all the members, FBLA Alumni, and past adviser Ms. Cink that have made Crete FBLA what it is today!

Life’s most persistent and urgent question is, WHAT ARE YOU DOING FOR OTHERS? ~Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

Crete Elementary served others by tying and making blankets for our community. They learned that even though their hands may be small, together we can do great things!

2nd graders prepared informational scripts about Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. They taught us that everyone has the ability to make a CHANGE in the world!

This day would not of been possible with out the help of the Doane Baseball Team, Cardinal Union and CCLC. THANK YOU!
#CardinalPride #MLKDay2020

post_text: The Crete NHS participated in the Crete Public Library’s Book Brigade on January 13th . The Cardinal Chapter of NHS, City of Crete, Patrons of the library, students from Crete Public School and many others passed on 2 books from the old library to the new one. They ended the brigade at the new library with water and cookies to celebrate the transition. The new library is opening towards the end of January. Over the past several years the Cardinal Chapter of NHS has donated to the new library fund and very excited for its opening as well.

post_text:
Five students from Crete Middle School competed in the semi-annual Noetic Learning Math Contest. The contest was conducted through the Enrichment program led by Mrs. Karen Drevo.

Noetic Learning Math Contest is a national mathematics contest for Elementary and Middle School students. The goal of the competition is to encourage students' interest in math, to develop their problem-solving skills, and to inspire them to excel in math.

More than 24,000 students representing 561 schools across the country took part in this fall’s contest.

The Cardinal Mathletes team consists of Nolan Miller, Alex Eltze, Ty Yeager, Corbin Coe, and Nick Eltze. Alex was the team winner

Congratulations to all five participants. The contest results demonstrate our students’ great problem-solving skills and math talents.

post_text: "PALS (Positive Attitude and Leadership by Students) is a school based mentoring program. There are 42 senior students, Sr. PALS, who volunteer to mentor a 5th grade student, Jr. PALS, each week. The seniors and fifth graders play board games, play sports in the gym or playground, and talk to one another. “The fifth grade students love spending time with their Sr. PAL. They tell me on a weekly basis that the time with their PAL goes way too fast! It is amazing that our very own high school students are making such a positive impact in their school community,” states Lisa Fye, the intermediate school principal. The Sr. PALS will have volunteered over 210 hours by the end of this semester."

post_text:
Crete TeamMates Receives a Walmart Giving Grant

We are excited to announce that Crete TeamMates received a grant from Walmart Giving! Crete Walmart, and store manager, Marie Sellers, are happy to support the Crete community and especially the youth of Crete, through their donation to the TeamMates mentoring program. Crete Walmart donated $1,000.00 to the Crete TeamMates. “I am grateful and excited for local businesses and leaders, like Crete Walmart and Marie Sellers, who are investing in the youth of Crete, through the TeamMates mentoring program,” said Wendy Byh Jongejan, high school TeamMates coordinator. The Crete TeamMates mentoring program will use the funds to support match activities like the crafts, the end of the year picnic, and general operational costs.#BetterTogether #WalmartGiving #Walmart

Marie Sellers (pictured left) is the Crete Walmart store manager. Wendy Byh Jongejan (pictured right) the Crete High School TeamMates Coordinator.

Our softball team is state bound! Crete will start their state title run at 9 AM on Wednesday. The official NSAA bracket can be found here. Our school schedule will be as follows-

Wednesday and Thursday - Regular school days. Any student who wishes to attend the state tournament must follow standard checkout procedures. Those students going to the tournament will be marked in Infinite Campus with an excused absence.

Friday - Our girls playing in the championship game on Friday will result in an 11:30 AM dismal. The championship game is at 2 PM. Two spirit buses (one at the middle school and one at the high school) will be provided for students to ride free of charge. Staff must report to the game or their building for the afternoon.

It's been a great season thus far. It's time to bring home a state title!

Dr. McDowell
#CardinalPride

post_text:
The following is the list of Student Council sponsored theme Days for Crete Middle School for September 16 to September 20:

Monday, September 16: Monochromatic Monday - Dress up all in ONE solid color for the day!!

Tuesday, September 17: Throwback Tuesday - Dress up in something from the past...Any time period or decade period.

Wednesday, September 18: Hobby Wednesday - Dress up as your favorite hobby...If you like sports dress up like your favorite sport or wear your favorite sports team gear, if you play video games dress up like a gamer, etc.

Thursday, September 19: Impersonation Thursday - This day you can dress up like someone else (you can twin with somebody or with a group of friends), you can also dress up like a famous person, or a teacher. Make sure you a positively impersonating others.

Friday, September, 20: Cardinal Pride Day - Wear RED or your favorite Crete Cardinals gear!!

post_text:
Special Education Nonpublic Consultation Notice

On August 19, 2019 at 1:00 pm, a meeting regarding special education services for nonpublic schools and home schools will be conducted by Crete Public Schools, at St. James Elementary, at 525 East 14th Street. The purpose of the meeting will be to provide an opportunity for parents who have parentally placed their child in an approved and/or accredited nonpublic school or exempt homeschool and representatives of nonpublic schools to participate in the development of a plan for providing special education services to children with disabilities within the Crete district for the 2019-2020 school year. Parents of a home-schooled child or a child attending a nonpublic school who has been or may be identified with a disability and will attend an approved and/or accredited nonpublic school within the boundaries of Crete Public Schools are urged to attend. Please RSVP your intention to attend to Diane Bruha, Director of Special Programs at 402-826-7895 or dianeb@creteschools.org.

With the first day of school, and new drivers learning the routes, we have some students being dropped off late. We do apologize for the inconvenience. We plan to have all the issues worked out and back to our set schedule as soon as possible.

Thank you so much for your support for the band program!
Jennene & Eric
